The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, visited California to discuss tax relief with families and business owners. He highlighted the devastating wildfires in the state and assured that the federal government would provide assistance. Pence mentioned that the Trump administration is committed to passing the largest tax cut in American history and outlined the key points of the tax relief plan. This includes cutting taxes for working families, simplifying the tax code, and making businesses more competitive. Pence expressed optimism about the economy and encouraged input from the gathered individuals to inform the ongoing debate in Washington, D.C.